sentences: Läänest pärit muusika on meile väga lähedane.
Põhja- ja Lääne-Eesti murded on erinevad.
context: The word 'lääne' is the genitive singular form of the Estonian noun 'lääs', meaning 'west' or 'western'. It indicates possession or origin from the west direction. In Estonian, this would typically be used to indicate something coming from or belonging to the western part of Estonia, Europe, or other geographical regions.
